caption: Slightly better than cafeteria food at high prices. Chicken teriyaki tough like a bike tire. I feel bamboozled by having gotten food here, especially when there are tons of legit Japanese places nearby. This is not a restaurant either, just a cloud kitchen where they make a bunch of heat-lamp stuff under various fly-by-night names.
Food was alright. Portion size was a bit small for the price. I paid 18 for salmon bento and it was basically a bowl with two gyoza.
